<p>How can I set the <code>SelectedItem</code> of a ListView in my Code? My problem is, that is isn't highlighted when I preselect an item in my code. The ListView is defined in the xaml file. </p>  <pre><code>&lt;ListView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}" SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}" /&gt; </code></pre>  <p>My ViewModel</p>  <pre><code>class MyViewModel {     List&lt;MyItem&gt; Items {get; set;}     MyItem SelectedItem { get; set; }      public MyViewModel()      {         Items = new List&lt;MyItem&gt;{ ... };         SelectedItem = Items.First();     } } </code></pre>  <p>But when I show the view, it is not highlighting the selected item. When I click on an item, it is highlighted and set correctly. I've played around with property changed, but this shouldn't have an effect, because the property is set right in the constructor.</p>